{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-08",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_08_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 8 - Horsefeathers",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 3,
  "page_total": 5,
  "page_start_sec": 491.48,
  "page_end_sec": 734.82,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.672,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 491.48,
      "end": 494.48,
      "text": "\"'I do not know what I should say,' he murmured.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 495.22,
      "end": 496.68,
      "text": "His embarrassment seemed genuine.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 498.112,
      "end": 500.42,
      "text": "\"'Try telling the facts,' Dundee suggested.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 501.696,
      "end": 502.48,
      "text": "\"'The facts?'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 503.68,
      "end": 504.88,
      "text": "Cairo's eyes fidgeted,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 504.94,
      "end": 507.86,
      "text": "though their gaze did not actually evade the lieutenant's."
    },
    {
      "start": 509.152,
      "end": 511.82,
      "text": "\"'What assurance have I that the facts will be believed?'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 512.8,
      "end": 513.48,
      "text": "\"'Quit stalling.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 514.28,
      "end": 516.06,
      "text": "All you've got to do is swear to a",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 516.06,
      "end": 517.6,
      "text": "complaint that they took a poke at you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 517.94,
      "end": 520.0,
      "text": "and the warrant clerk will believe you enough to"
    },
    {
      "start": 520.0,
      "end": 522.23,
      "text": "issue a warrant that'll let us throw them in the can.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 523.744,
      "end": 525.62,
      "text": "Spade spoke in an amused tone.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 526.432,
      "end": 526.86,
      "text": "\"'Go ahead,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 526.94,
      "end": 527.24,
      "text": "Cairo."
    },
    {
      "start": 527.92,
      "end": 528.58,
      "text": "Make him happy.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 529.26,
      "end": 530.12,
      "text": "Tell him you'll do it,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 530.16,
      "end": 532.22,
      "text": "and then we'll swear to one against you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 532.34,
      "end": 534.12,
      "text": "and he'll have the lot of us.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 535.328,
      "end": 537.96,
      "text": "Cairo cleared his throat and looked nervously around the room,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 538.432,
      "end": 539.58,
      "text": "not into the eyes of anyone"
    },
    {
      "start": 539.78,
      "end": 539.96,
      "text": "there."
    },
    {
      "start": 541.376,
      "end": 542.94,
      "text": "Dundee blew breath through his nose in a",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 542.94,
      "end": 545.04,
      "text": "puff that was not quite a snort and said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 546.22,
      "end": 546.95,
      "text": "\"'Get your hats.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 548.288,
      "end": 548.92,
      "text": "Cairo's eyes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 549.16,
      "end": 550.58,
      "text": "holding worry and a question,"
    },
    {
      "start": 550.76,
      "end": 552.66,
      "text": "met Spade's mocking gaze."
    },
    {
      "start": 553.76,
      "end": 556.72,
      "text": "Spade winked at him and sat on the arm of the padded rocker.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 557.88,
      "end": 558.38,
      "text": "\"'Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 558.38,
      "end": 559.92,
      "text": "boys and girls,' he said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 559.96,
      "end": 562.1,
      "text": "grinning at the Levantine and at the girl with nothing"
    },
    {
      "start": 562.3,
      "end": 564.28,
      "text": "but delight in his voice and in his grin,"
    },
    {
      "start": 565.3,
      "end": 566.49,
      "text": "\"'We put it over nicely.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 568.256,
      "end": 570.96,
      "text": "Dundee's hard square face darkened the least of shades.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 571.56,
      "end": 573.44,
      "text": "He repeated peremptorily,"
    },
    {
      "start": 574.176,
      "end": 575.19,
      "text": "\"'Get your hats.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 576.736,
      "end": 578.2,
      "text": "Spade turned his grin on the lieutenant,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 578.74,
      "end": 581.44,
      "text": "squirmed into a more comfortable position on the chair arm,"
    },
    {
      "start": 581.68,
      "end": 582.56,
      "text": "and asked lazily,"
    },
    {
      "start": 583.84,
      "end": 585.53,
      "text": "\"'Don't you know when you're being kidded?'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 586.92,
      "end": 589.22,
      "text": "Tom Polehouse's face grew red and shiny.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 590.176,
      "end": 590.76,
      "text": "Dundee's face,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 590.96,
      "end": 591.82,
      "text": "still darkening,"
    },
    {
      "start": 591.96,
      "end": 592.76,
      "text": "was immobile,"
    },
    {
      "start": 592.92,
      "end": 595.44,
      "text": "except for his lips moving stiffly to say,"
    },
    {
      "start": 596.23,
      "end": 596.68,
      "text": "No,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 596.88,
      "end": 599.1,
      "text": "but we'll let that wait till we get down to the hall."
    },
    {
      "start": 600.544,
      "end": 602.54,
      "text": "Spade rose and put his hands in his pockets.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 603.232,
      "end": 605.5,
      "text": "He stood erect so that he might look that much",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 605.6,
      "end": 606.78,
      "text": "farther down at the lieutenant."
    },
    {
      "start": 608.08,
      "end": 609.24,
      "text": "His grin was a taunt,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 609.72,
      "end": 611.62,
      "text": "and self-certainty spoke in every line"
    },
    {
      "start": 611.62,
      "end": 612.28,
      "text": "of his carriage."
    },
    {
      "start": 613.76,
      "end": 615.12,
      "text": "I dare you to take us in,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 615.22,
      "end": 615.5,
      "text": "Dundee,"
    },
    {
      "start": 616.0,
      "end": 616.32,
      "text": "he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 617.024,
      "end": 618.1,
      "text": "We'll laugh at you in every",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 618.26,
      "end": 619.5,
      "text": "newspaper in San Francisco."
    },
    {
      "start": 620.62,
      "end": 623.5,
      "text": "You don't think any of us is going to swear to any complaints against",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 623.6,
      "end": 623.94,
      "text": "the others,"
    },
    {
      "start": 624.06,
      "end": 624.4,
      "text": "do you?"
    },
    {
      "start": 624.56,
      "end": 625.62,
      "text": "Wake up!"
    },
    {
      "start": 625.86,
      "end": 626.98,
      "text": "You've been kidded."
    },
    {
      "start": 627.96,
      "end": 628.68,
      "text": "When the bell rang,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 628.86,
      "end": 629.99,
      "text": "I said to Miss O'Shaughnessy"
    },
    {
      "start": 630.22,
      "end": 630.7,
      "text": "and Cairo,"
    },
    {
      "start": 630.88,
      "end": 632.8,
      "text": "it's those damned bulls again."
    },
    {
      "start": 633.06,
      "end": 634.52,
      "text": "They're getting to be nuisances."
    },
    {
      "start": 635.936,
      "end": 636.8,
      "text": "Let's play a joke on",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 636.92,
      "end": 637.04,
      "text": "them."
    },
    {
      "start": 637.35,
      "end": 638.36,
      "text": "When you hear them going,"
    },
    {
      "start": 638.58,
      "end": 639.44,
      "text": "one of you scream,"
    },
    {
      "start": 639.74,
      "end": 642.12,
      "text": "and then we'll see how far we can string them"
    },
    {
      "start": 642.24,
      "end": 643.32,
      "text": "along before they tumble."
    },
    {
      "start": 643.6,
      "end": 644.52,
      "text": "And—'"
    },
    {
      "start": 645.088,
      "end": 647.42,
      "text": "Bridget O'Shaughnessy bent forward in her chair and"
    },
    {
      "start": 647.56,
      "end": 648.9,
      "text": "began to laugh hysterically."
    },
    {
      "start": 650.08,
      "end": 651.36,
      "text": "Cairo started and smiled.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 652.36,
      "end": 654.1,
      "text": "There was no vitality in his smile,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 654.26,
      "end": 655.96,
      "text": "but he held it fixed on his face."
    },
    {
      "start": 656.66,
      "end": 657.26,
      "text": "Tom,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 657.28,
      "end": 657.9,
      "text": "glowering,"
    },
    {
      "start": 657.9,
      "end": 658.2,
      "text": "grumbled."
    },
    {
      "start": 659.136,
      "end": 659.58,
      "text": "\"'Cut it out,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 659.68,
      "end": 660.28,
      "text": "Sam.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 661.152,
      "end": 662.24,
      "text": "Spade chuckled and said.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 663.008,
      "end": 664.54,
      "text": "\"'But that's the way it was.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 665.18,
      "end": 668.6,
      "text": "We—' And the cut on his head and mouth?' Dundee asked"
    },
    {
      "start": 668.96,
      "end": 669.48,
      "text": "imperturbably."
    },
    {
      "start": 669.66,
      "end": 671.08,
      "text": "Where'd they come from?"
    },
    {
      "start": 672.224,
      "end": 672.66,
      "text": "Ask him,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 672.86,
      "end": 673.84,
      "text": "Spade suggested."
    },
    {
      "start": 674.14,
      "end": 676.26,
      "text": "Maybe he cut himself shaving."
    },
    {
      "start": 677.856,
      "end": 680.16,
      "text": "Cairo spoke quickly before he could be questioned,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 680.36,
      "end": 681.78,
      "text": "and the muscles of his face"
    },
    {
      "start": 681.88,
      "end": 683.38,
      "text": "quivered under the strain of holding"
    },
    {
      "start": 683.38,
      "end": 685.08,
      "text": "his smile in place while he spoke."
    },
    {
      "start": 686.34,
      "end": 686.88,
      "text": "I fell.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 687.15,
      "end": 690.28,
      "text": "We intended to be struggling for the pistol when you came in,"
    },
    {
      "start": 690.36,
      "end": 691.14,
      "text": "but I fell."
    },
    {
      "start": 692.34,
      "end": 694.48,
      "text": "I tripped on the end of the rug and fell",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 694.48,
      "end": 696.08,
      "text": "while we were pretending to struggle."
    },
    {
      "start": 696.28,
      "end": 698.08,
      "text": "Dundee said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 698.944,
      "end": 699.48,
      "text": "Horse feathers.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 700.704,
      "end": 701.16,
      "text": "Spade said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 701.952,
      "end": 702.52,
      "text": "That's all right,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 702.52,
      "end": 702.82,
      "text": "Dundee."
    },
    {
      "start": 702.92,
      "end": 703.96,
      "text": "Believe it or not."
    },
    {
      "start": 704.52,
      "end": 707.68,
      "text": "The point is that that's our story and we'll stick to it."
    },
    {
      "start": 708.32,
      "end": 711.26,
      "text": "The newspapers will print it whether they believe it or not,"
    },
    {
      "start": 711.54,
      "end": 713.96,
      "text": "and it'll be just as funny one way as the other."
    },
    {
      "start": 715.0,
      "end": 715.98,
      "text": "What are you going to do about it?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 716.62,
      "end": 717.98,
      "text": "It's no crime to kid a copper,"
    },
    {
      "start": 718.08,
      "end": 718.32,
      "text": "is it?"
    },
    {
      "start": 719.16,
      "end": 720.96,
      "text": "You haven't got anything on anybody here.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 721.6,
      "end": 723.46,
      "text": "Everything we've told you was part of the joke."
    },
    {
      "start": 724.4,
      "end": 725.58,
      "text": "What are you going to do about it?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 727.008,
      "end": 729.74,
      "text": "Dundee put his back to Spade and gripped Cairo by the shoulders.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 731.06,
      "end": 733.6,
      "text": "\"'You can't get away with that,' he snarled,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 733.68,
      "end": 734.82,
      "text": "shaking the Levantine."
    }
  ]
}